Title: The Canonical Symmetry and Hamiltonian Formalism. II. Hamiltonian

OperatorsAuthors: A. N. Leznov and A. V. Razumov

Comments: 13 pages, LaTeX file, IHEP 93-69

It is shown how the canonical symmetry is used to look for the hierarchy ofthe Hamiltonian operators relevant to the system under consideration. Itappears that only the invariance condition can be used to solve the problem.